# Fixture

## Summary

Fixture models a non-seating floor element placed on the same canvas as the tables — the `kind` enum covers plants, trees, a balloon arch, stage, projector, red carpet, dance floor, ceremony arch, cake table, bar, and abstract curved-wall/rectangle/circle decor shapes. Its schema is a `label` string, the `kind` enum, a `pattern` enum (solid/outline/soft) that controls how the glyph fills, canvas geometry (`x`, `y`, `width`, `height`, `rotation`, `z` — all numbers), a `locked` boolean that pins it against moving or resizing on the canvas, and a `color`. A computed `title` falls back from the label to the kind's display label. The planner holds fixtures in a containsMany field so decor travels with the seating plan.

## Import

```js
import { Fixture } from '../fixture';
```

## Usage as a Field

```ts
@field fixtures = containsMany(Fixture);
```

## Template Usage

```handlebars
{{#each @model.fixtures as |fixture|}}
  {{fixture.title}}
{{/each}}
```

Each entry also renders with its own embedded and fitted views via `<@fields.fixtures />`.
